<a href='http://www.ukclimbing.com/news/item.php?id=70949' title='Read full story'><img src='https://cdn.ukclimbing.com/t/289291.jpg' width='150' height='105' alt='thumb' border='1' align='left' hspace='8' /></a>On his third trip to Bishop, and after specialized training, Toru Nakajima has managed to make the 4th ascent of Paul Robinson's Lucid Dreaming, ~8C. 

Paul made the first ascent in late March 2010, and it has since been repeated by Daniel Woods and Alex Megos. Initially, ~8C+ was suggested, but Paul changed his mind long before Daniel made the 2nd ascent.

After 16days efforts, three seasons, finally I did my long standing project Lucid Dreaming!! We arrived in Bishop the15th but rain kept...